      "target": {
        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "fix(gateway): guard formatAuditList against non-string items to prevent handshake trim crash (#90654)",
        "body": "## Summary\nCLI write commands (`openclaw message send`, `broadcast`, `probe`) crash the gateway WebSocket handshake with `TypeError: Cannot read properties of undefined (reading 'trim')` when the device pairing state contains non-string entries in roles/scopes arrays.\n\nThe root cause is `formatAuditList` in `src/gateway/server/ws-connection/message-handler.ts` calling `.trim()` on array items without first verifying they are strings. When legacy or malformed pairing data reaches the gateway connect path, the unguarded `.trim()` throws and the socket is closed before the handshake completes.\n\n## Changes\n- `src/gateway/server/ws-connection/message-handler.ts`: Extract `formatAuditList` to module-level, add `typeof item === \\\"string\\\"` guard before `.trim()`, matching the pattern already used for sibling fields like `nonce`/`instanceId`.\n- `src/gateway/server/ws-connection/message-handler.post-connect-health.test.ts`: Add regression tests covering empty arrays, valid strings, non-string items (undefined, null, numbers), and all-empty/non-string inputs.\n- `scripts/repro/issue-90654-gateway-handshake-trim-crash.mts`: Standalone reproduction script.\n\n## Real behavior proof\n\n- **Behavior addressed**: `formatAuditList` no longer crashes when iterating over arrays containing non-string items.\n- **Real environment tested**: Linux x64, Node v24.15.0, OpenClaw repo at main.\n- **Exact steps or command run after this patch**:\n  - `node --import tsx scripts/repro/issue-90654-gateway-handshake-trim-crash.mts`\n  - `node scripts/run-vitest.mjs src/gateway/server/ws-connection/message-handler.post-connect-health.test.ts --run`\n- **Evidence after fix**:\n  ```text\n  === Reproduction for issue #90654 ===\n  Valid cases:\n    undefined: <none>\n    empty: <none>\n    normal: a,b,c\n  Malformed input (contains non-string items):\n    Input: [ 'valid', undefined, null, 42, 'also-valid' ]\n    Result: also-valid,valid\n  PASS: Non-string items are safely skipped.\n  ```\n  Test results: 84 passed (4 test files).\n- **Observed result after fix**: `formatAuditList` silently skips non-string items and continues processing valid strings. No TypeError is thrown.\n- **What was not tested**: Live gateway handshake with actual malformed pairing state on a running gateway instance.\n\n## Verification\n- `node scripts/run-vitest.mjs src/gateway/server/ws-connection/message-handler.post-connect-health.test.ts --run` → 84 passed\n- `npx oxlint --import-plugin --config .oxlintrc.json src/gateway/server/ws-connection/message-handler.ts` → clean\n- `node --import tsx scripts/repro/issue-90654-gateway-handshake-trim-crash.mts` → PASS\n\n🤖 AI-assisted PR",
        "branch": "fix/90654-gateway-handshake-trim-crash",
